    "facebook_testimonials_MJgqMM": {
      "type": "facebook-testimonials",
      "blocks": {
        "column_twDwFz": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "post_author": "Carlos Rodriguez",
            "post_author_avatar": "shopify://shop_images/images_21_430x_cdcca66f-ecf2-4af6-b58e-2a1ff9345830.jpg",
            "post_author_verified": true,
            "post_time": "10h ago",
            "post_text": "<p>I just finished <em>The 2012 Blackfile</em> and I’m honestly unsettled. Not because it’s scary… but because it reads like someone in 2012 genuinely predicted everything happening right now. Pandemics, conflicts, AI, geopolitical shifts it’s all in there.</p>",
            "post_reactions": "like,wow",
            "post_reactions_text": "411",
            "post_comments_text": "26 Comments",
            "comment_1_author": "Comment author",
            "comment_1_author_verified": false,
            "comment_1_time": "2h ago",
            "comment_1_text": "",
            "comment_2_author": "Comment author",
            "comment_2_author_verified": false,
            "comment_2_time": "3h ago",
            "comment_2_text": ""
          }
        },
        "column_wbB73q": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "post_author": "Jennifer Thompson",
            "post_author_avatar": "shopify://shop_images/openart-a-hyper-realistic-full-body-portrait-of-a-beautiful-19-year-old-lonodon-gi_430x_99a8b6ab-bde8-4986-9a20-6d5ff9b5af0a.webp",
            "post_author_verified": true,
            "post_time": "2h ago",
            "post_text": "<p>This book is wild. The writing style is so clinical and precise that it really feels like you’re reading a leaked intelligence document. The chapters about AI and the global conflicts gave me chills because they match the timeline we’re in almost too perfectly.</p>",
            "post_reactions": "like, love,wow",
            "post_reactions_text": "1.1k",
            "post_comments_text": "26 Comments",
            "comment_1_author": "Comment author",
            "comment_1_author_verified": false,
            "comment_1_time": "2h ago",
            "comment_1_text": "",
            "comment_2_author": "Comment author",
            "comment_2_author_verified": false,
            "comment_2_time": "3h ago",
            "comment_2_text": ""
          }
        },
        "column_Ub3CUR": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "post_author": "Eliot Wicken",
            "post_author_avatar": "shopify://shop_images/download_1_430x_6dfdcfb2-fc7f-4549-b51f-c4f6f61107a6.jpg",
            "post_author_verified": false,
            "post_time": "14d ago",
            "post_text": "<p>I’m not easily impressed, but this book got me. It breaks down world events in a way that makes everything suddenly make sense. The predictions about media manipulation, economic instability, and northern migration hit hard. It’s like someone mapped out the next 20 years in advance. Definitely a book I’ll reread — and keep close.</p>",
            "post_reactions": "wow,like",
            "post_reactions_text": "2.3k",
            "post_comments_text": "59 Comments",
            "comment_1_author": "Comment author",
            "comment_1_author_verified": false,
            "comment_1_time": "2h ago",
            "comment_1_text": "",
            "comment_2_author": "Comment author",
